## LLMRouter Architecture

**Provider-agnostic contract (all engine files call ONLY this):**
```js
LLMRouter.run(engineName, payload)
  → Promise<{ output: Object, model: string, cost_usd: number, duration_ms: number }>
```
In demo: resolves to WebGPU/WebLLM provider.
In production: identical interface routes to Pathwaize backend HTTP endpoint.
Adding a new provider = one config entry, not a rebuild.

**Model constants (verbatim — demo-builder must use exactly these IDs):**
```js
const PRIMARY_MODEL  = "Qwen2.5-7B-Instruct-q4f16_1-MLC";
const ROUTER_MODEL   = "Qwen2.5-1.5B-Instruct-q4f16_1-MLC";
const FALLBACK_MODEL = "Qwen2.5-3B-Instruct-q4f16_1-MLC";
```

**Init sequence:**
1. Check `navigator.gpu` — if undefined, enable mock-LLM mode (canned responses, full workflow visible).
2. Query WebGPU adapter; if VRAM estimated < 5GB, default to FALLBACK_MODEL with "Compact model for your hardware" banner.
3. Load PRIMARY_MODEL; show prominent download progress bar ("Loading AI model — first load ~30s; cached on return"). This is P0 UX — users will close if they think nothing is happening.
4. Load ROUTER_MODEL in background after primary ready.

**Structured output enforcement:**
- Every routing and generation step: `response_format: { type: "json_object" }` (WebLLM grammar enforcement blocks illegal tokens).
- JS validates schema after each step. On failure: 1 reflection retry ("Your output failed with error X. Rewrite correctly."). After 2nd failure: inline error card ("Generation failed — re-run").

**Context management:**
- Sliding window: cap at 5 turns per engine run.
- Workspace context (persistent intelligence) injected as system prompt prefix on every call.

---

## Engine Pipelines (strict prompt chaining — no free ReAct loops)

### Authority Engine (Priority 1)

**Step 1 — Route (ROUTER_MODEL):**
System: "Classify this user request."
Output schema: `{ "engine": "authority", "platform": "linkedin|twitter|general", "topic": "...", "tone": "authoritative|conversational|educational", "angle": "..." }`

**Step 2 — Generate (PRIMARY_MODEL):**
System: "You are a ghostwriter for a real estate investor building authority on [platform]. Context: [workspace.context]. Write [platform]-optimized content. No em dashes."
Output schema:
```json
{ "content": "string", "word_count": "number", "hashtags": ["string"], "cta": "string" }
```

**Step 3 — JS validate:** check content exists, hashtags is array, word_count > 50. 1 reflection retry on fail.

**Output card actions:** [Request Edits → revision textarea → Re-generate] | [Approve] | (only after Approve:) [Push to LinkedIn/X → mock toast receipt]
Push button rendered `disabled` + tooltip "Approve first" until status === "approved".

---

### Newsletter Engine (Priority 2)

**Step 1 — Route (ROUTER_MODEL):**
Output schema: `{ "engine": "newsletter", "topic": "...", "audience": "...", "tone": "...", "brand_voice": "..." }`

**Step 2 — Generate (PRIMARY_MODEL):**
System: "Generate a complete newsletter for [audience] in real estate investing. Context: [workspace.context]. No em dashes."
Output schema:
```json
{
  "body": "string",
  "subject_lines": ["string", "string", "string"],
  "preview_text": "string",
  "word_count": "number"
}
```

**UI specifics:** 3 subject-line options rendered as selectable radio cards; user picks one before Approve. Preview text editable inline.
**Actions:** [Request Edits] | [Approve] | (after Approve:) [Schedule/Push → mock "Queued for delivery" receipt]

---

### Knowledge Engine Lite (Priority 3)

**Step 1 — Route (ROUTER_MODEL):**
Output schema: `{ "engine": "knowledge", "topic": "...", "context": "...", "category": "process|playbook|faq|definition" }`

**Step 2 — Generate (PRIMARY_MODEL):**
System: "Generate a business knowledge base entry for a real estate investor. Context: [workspace.context]. Format as structured markdown. No em dashes."
Output schema:
```json
{ "title": "string", "content": "string", "tags": ["string"], "format": "markdown" }
```

**Destination picker (visible before Push):** [Google Drive] | [GitHub Repo] — two button options.
**Actions:** [Request Edits] | [Approve] | (after Approve + destination selected:) [Save] → mock receipt:
- Drive: `{ fileId: "1XyZ...", path: "/Pathwaize KB/[title].md", url: "https://drive.google.com/file/d/1XyZ..." }`
- GitHub: `{ sha: "a3f9d12", branch: "main", path: "kb/[slug].md", url: "https://github.com/pathwaize/knowledge-base/commit/a3f9d12" }`

