## Scope Fences

- No real API keys, no exposed LLM credentials (WebGPU = local; mock-LLM fallback for non-WebGPU)
- No real Google Drive/GitHub/LinkedIn push (all mocked with realistic receipt UI)
- No advanced analytics, no continuous KB monitoring, no proactive gap detection
- Intel Brief = static demo data only (client explicitly calls this out for V1)
- 12 files exactly, no bundler, no build step
- WebLLM models load from CDN at runtime (not bundled, no 3-minute build timeout risk)
- No mw-backend blueprint needed

---

## Risks + Mitigations

| Risk | Mitigation |
|---|---|
| 7B model OOM on low-VRAM GPUs | Auto-detect adapter; fall back to 3B with "Compact model for your hardware" banner |
| First-load 30s model download | Prominent progress bar (P0 UX); OPFS cache so return loads < 5s |
| WebGPU unavailable (non-Chrome, mobile) | Mock-LLM mode: canned high-quality responses; full workflow demonstrable |
| JSON generation failures from smaller model | Grammar enforcement + 1-retry reflection; inline error card after 2nd failure |
| GHL postMessage spec not public | Demo uses URL params + mock wrapper; proposal notes real GHL dev access required for production |
| Mock canned responses look low-quality | Pre-write realistic, high-quality canned responses for all 3 engines before enabling mock-LLM path |

